description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a deputy ward manager to support the development of our inpatient dementia services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will demonstrate excellent leadership skills and will be passionate about working with people with dementia their relatives/carers. They will be fully committed to providing innovative care and treatment that is evidence based within a specialist dementia unit. Working as part of a multidisciplinary team including Consultant Psychology, Nurse Consultant, Occupational Therapy, Physiotherapy and Psychiatrist of Old Age you will support the team in delivering a personalised approach to care and treatment aimed and promoting the health and well-being of people with dementia in our care. The service offers excellent training opportunities to all staff and this post is supported by a clinical manager for dementia inpatient care who is based on the wards.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to recruit a positive and motivated leader who will be able to help us to provide the best care possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Williams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen.williams51@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01208 251344&lt;/p&gt;
